color=#FFE081>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.elvenelite.com/images/cellpic3.gif class=headings><font color=#FFE081>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#BA9F70><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ukupwerstix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kupwerstix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scribe</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(5/26/02 9:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revenge</span><hr size=1> Neriak- A strange Dark Elf walked into the commons. His gold armor was indeed odd for a normal Dark Elf , but this was not a normal Dark Elf. Kupwerstix , using his mask of deception, walked among the teir'dal with ease. He so  was blinded by anger and grief that he did not think about how out of place he seemed here. As he entered the Third Gate a group of guards approached him. &quot; What is your name and house commoner?&quot; one of the guards asked him. &quot; My name is Khelben of House Zzporza&quot;. Kupwerstix replied. &quot;Never heard of you.... in fact I have never heard of House Zzporza now that i think about it&quot; one guard said.&quot; I don't think you are a Dark Elf at all&quot;. Kupwerstix, knowing his cover was blown, decided to take the chance to strike now. Pulling out his blade and Mace, he started a song of victory,giving him strength and speed. He cut through the guards with ease, but he knew he did not have much time now. He pulled out his drum and started to sing a song of speed but he found he could not move, for his feet were bound in roots. He turned to see a group or Wizards laughing at him , as they all began to cast their spells. Knowing his time was up he took one last desperate chance and let his back and let loose a desperate dirge at them knocking all of them off their feet. Kupwerstix grinned, but only for a moment.All he felt was a sharp pain, when the mace struck him in the back of the head. He fell hard to the cold floor unconscious. He later awoke in a small cell guarded by 4 guards. This has not been a good day.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#AB8C5B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ublahg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blahg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scribe Master</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(5/27/02 1:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revenge</span><hr size=1> Blahg wandered through the forest, lost and alone.  Looking back, it would have been wise to hire a halfling guide to help him sneak near the city of Neriak.  Having been in too big of a hurry to catch up with Kupwerstix, he hurried on alone and took a wrong turn.<br>
<br>
Blahg sat down near a tree, wishing that Elrax or Lenian was with.  Surely one of them would know how to get to the city!  <br>
<br>
Just as he stood up to continue his search for the Dark Elf city, an axe slammed into the tree above his head, and the fight was on.  The guards had found him! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#BA9F70><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ulenianpuremyst.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenian Puremyst</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 702<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(5/29/02 9:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revenge</span><hr size=1> Distracted by the foul stench of the dark Nek forest and thoughts of Blahg's story of the missing Bard Kuperstix, Lenian headed towards the bridge without magics to conceal his being there.  The concerned look was well warranted as Lenian knew what evils the Dark Elves were capable of doing to a prisoner.  His next thoughts were interupted...<br>
<br>
&quot;Die, Tresspasser!&quot; yelled the dark elf guard as his attack was quickly sidestepped by the Ranger.  &quot;I'm in no mood for this inkie!&quot; mumbled Lenian as he called on Karana's blessing to slow the Dark Elf to a crawl.  Looking over his shoulder, Lenian noticed 2 more guards on the other side of the bridge oblivious to what was happening.  &quot;Maybe we can make this...  more entertaining&quot;  thought Lenian with a grin.  <br>
<br>
Within a few moments, 2 arrows, and a few prayers to Karana, Lenian had 3 guards in a neat row being held in place by roots.  Ancient elvish words flowed from Lenians lips as one guard was was enveloped by flames and quickly dispatched with a few tactical blows by the Rangers Wurmslayer.  The remaining two guards glanced at one another with concerned looks.  &quot;I am the least of your worries Inkies...  Be Afaid!&quot;  Lenian said as he charged at one of his foes.  Bits of armor flew through the air still electrified from Swiftwinds enchantment.  Breathing his last breath, the guards body plunged into the river hissing and bubbling as it sank.<br>
<br>
Spinning to end this little distraction, Lenian saw that his ensnaring roots spell had dropped and the remaining guard running across the bridge to get help.  Lenian lets out an audible sigh. &quot;Will they ever learn?&quot;  <br>
<br>
The guard, reaching the end of the bridge thinking he was home free... &lt;zip&gt;&lt;zip&gt;&lt;zip&gt;  three silver tipped arrows plunge through his armor nearly ending his life.<br>
<br>
Walking up to the near dead Dark Elf, Lenian raises his sword to finally end this little game and go about his business. &quot;Wait...  I have better plans for you evil elf!&quot;  Lenian says with an amused grin.<br>
<br>
Sounds of electricity and scratching can be heard as Lenian knelt over the guard.  &quot;There!  Now go to your dark city with that message!&quot;  Picking the bleeding Inkie up by the scruff of his neck the Half Elf adds...  &quot;And know that your life was spared for one reason and one reason only!&quot;  &quot;Now GO!&quot;  Lenian yells kicking the evil guard.  <br>
<br>
What can be see engraved in highly visable huge letters across the guards chest piece were two simple letters....  They were  &quot;EE&quot;.<br>
